The paper discusses the challenges and solutions for managing distributed applications across multiple cloud environments, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of service-oriented architecture and component-based design, which falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the challenges of provisioning, elasticity, and high availability, which falls under the category of Computer Systems Organization (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of standards such as OASIS Service Component Architecture, which falls under the category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the proposed solution on various cloud providers, which falls under the category of Computing and Computation (cs.CC).
